Notes about scripts in the "make" directory  (Updated 2026-01-18)
----------------------------------------------------------------

BUILD SYSTEM FOR ACE COMPILER
-----------------------------

Makefile-ace    - GNU Makefile for building the ACE compiler.
                  Requires GNU Make 3.80+ and ADE shell environment.
                  Usage: make -f Makefile-ace
                         make -f Makefile-ace V=1    (verbose)
                         make -f Makefile-ace clean  (clean build)


LIBRARY BUILD SCRIPTS
---------------------

lcmake          - Compile a C library module

lmake           - Assemble an assembly code library module or join all
                  library modules together to form db.lib

makelib         - Assembles a single assembly code module to create a
                  linked library file (used to create startup.lib).
                  See also src/lib/startup/make.

makedb          - Creates db.lib from the C and assembly source files in
                  src/lib/c and src/lib/asm.


OTHER SCRIPTS
-------------

asm             - Assemble a single assembly file

cmakep          - Compile with profiling support
